We should allow the option to format the Expand Macro's title such that it can be for example: a heading. This will allow us to anchor link to the macro easily. Example:
{code}
h2. {expand:title=Click here to see the text...}
This text block will expand and collapse.
{expand}
{code}
This is not possible currently, but gives an idea of what we're trying to accomplish here.

Create a page, copy and paste the following text in the editor.

{code}
[A|http://A/B]&nbsp;([C|http://asdasdsad/xxx..yyy])
{code}

Chrome crashes after a while.

On the other hand, Firefox works ok.

