In Confluence pages, it is possible to add [linking to attachments|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Linking+to+Attachments]. However if we removed the linked attachment, the text link will be greyed out, and it's not possible to edit or unlink the 'broken' link. And thus, a possible workaround for this is to remove the link itself, and replace it back with a normal text.

It will be nice if we have the option to unlink the broken link.

