Customers are reporting that the wiki markup conversion tasks do not run when upgrading from Confluence 3.5 directly to Confluence 4.2. The tasks do run when converting from 3.5 to 4.1 and then 4.2.

See comments on the 4.2 upgrade notes:
http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Confluence+4.2+Upgrade+Notes?focusedCommentId=283640878

* {quote}
Anonymous

The same question!

Tried 3.5.7->4.2 in test env, it looks like there were not any data conversion from wikimarkup to xhtml
{quote}

* {quote}

    Apr 12, 2012
    Sarah Maddox [Atlassian Technical Writer]

    Hallo there

    I've had a chat to the engineers, and the upgrade process should handle the wiki markup conversion when upgrading from Confluence 3.5.7 straight to 4.2. Please would you raise a support request at http://support.atlassian.com, so that our support engineers can help with the upgrade.

    Cheers, Sarah
{quote}
     
* {quote}
Harald Mueller

We've tried Upgrade 3.5.9 to 4.2 and there did not come up tasks to convert wiki markup. Also f.e. the code for Scaffolding plugin got lost.

Doing the path 3.5.9 -> 4.1.9 -> 4.2 on the 4.1.9 stage the markup upgrade ran and then the upgrade to 4.2 succeed (also for Scaffolding)
{quote}

