Using the previous Confluence user management (prior to 3.5 release) we are able to use to ID to access Confluence and Confluence consider it as one users.

This allow our users who don't know their other registered ID on LDAP server able to log-in to Confluence using the second CN without any issue in regards to their membership.

This behavior is not possible on the new user management. It would be great if Confluence can stored the second CN on database which result to the same behavior as previous user management.

