The vote macro still exists but only works via the "Wiki Markup" macro.

Workaround for this is to use Insert > Wiki Markup 
and in there put your 
{code}
{vote:My title}
a
b
c
{vote}
{code}

*Problem Description*
Export page to word in Confluence 4.2 and 4.2.1 shows the content incorrectly, it seems like the html that is generated did not rendered correctly.

*Findings*
The issue didn't affect MS Office 2007, but it affects Open Office. The tags generated has '3D' before the quotation mark, after equal sign. For example it is generated like.
{noformat}
http-equiv=3D"Content-Type" 
{noformat}
Instead of
{noformat}
http-equiv="Content-Type"
{noformat}

For more information, please refer to the following attachment, based on Confluence 4.2 release notes.

